Prostomium longer than wide, slightly wider anteriorly (
Fig. 46B, C
). Palps and lateral antennae collapsed, not manipulated to avoid further damage. Median antenna broken, basal region visible, inserted between posterior eyes. Anterior eyes twice larger than posterior ones, slightly more distant to each other than posterior ones; in lateral view, eyes almost fused.

Pharynx partially exposed (
Fig. 46D
